			<h3 ><a href="#p51">Re: Commentary: The Inequality Delusion</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=51#p51"><img src="./styles/thedruidsgrove/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=57">Tudamorf</a></strong> &raquo; Sat Oct 23, 2010 3:28 pm </p>

			

			<div class="content"><blockquote><div><cite>Zute wrote:</cite>People support the abstract goal of equality, it seems, while staunchly opposing specific government measures—whether increasing tax rates or limiting executive pay—designed to impose it.</div></blockquote><br />Psychologists are so obtuse.<br /><br />Just because people <span style="text-decoration: underline">SAY</span> they want equality on some survey doesn't mean they really want it.<br /><br />They're just saying it because they think it's what other people would like them to say.<br /><br />As to those Communists who convince themselves that everyone should be equal, I'd like to see their views after I slash their standard of living to that of a poor third world country -- which is exactly what it would be without all the rich people funding their military, their infrastructure, and their public services.<br /><br />Talk about biting the hand that feeds you.</div>

			

		</div>

		
