			<h3 ><a href="#p66">Re: Commentary: The Inequality Delusion</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=66#p66"><img src="./styles/thedruidsgrove/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=57">Tudamorf</a></strong> &raquo; Mon Oct 25, 2010 3:43 pm </p>

			

			<div class="content"><blockquote><div><cite>Fyyr wrote:</cite>Of course you had(and have) the same opportunity.</div></blockquote><br />So wrong.<br /><br />To make it work, you need to have the right idea, at the right place, at the right time, a lot of luck, and often plenty of money.<br /><br />The mere suggestion that everyone has equal opportunities is stupid.<br /><br />That's like saying you have the same opportunity as Michael Phelps does to win a medal in swimming.  Yeah technically, you both have the same opportunity to jump in the pool, but you are not similarly situated, even remotely.</div>

			

		</div>

		
